  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "それは22XX年のこと…\n\nレプリロイドの伝説的な英雄、Xとゼロは、悪のシグマを遥か昔に打ち倒し、マーベリックウイルスの発生を防ぐために新しい軍隊が作られました。しかし、時が経つにつれて、その軍隊は抑圧的になり、偏執的な正義を振るうようになりました。彼らの指導者はかつて偉大な戦士でしたが、今では冷酷で計算高い存在となり、彼に逆らうレプリロイドを排除しています。\n\nこの暗い時代には英雄が必要であり、シエルと彼女の反乱者グループは古代の遺跡でそれを見つけました…未来に生まれ変わった過去の英雄を。\n\nゼロは知らない時代にやってきました。過去の影からこの時代を救うために…自由の運命は彼の肩にかかっています。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Mega Man Zero is a hack and slash platform game series in Capcom's Mega Man video game franchise. It was developed by Inti Creates, with Co-Producer Keiji Inafune and Director Yoshinori Kawano. The series consists of four games that were first released on the Game Boy Advance and later on the Nintendo DS and the Virtual Console (Wii U).\nThe story takes place more than 100 years after the Mega Man X storyline and follows the re-awakened Zero, who is fighting in a war between humans and Reploids, self-aware, human-like robots who are oppressed and hunted down by mankind due to a worldwide energy shortage crisis. Together with the human scientist Ciel, Zero helps the Reploid resistance survive and fights against other Reploids sent by mankind to destroy them. However, this is only the setup for the story and events change drastically throughout the series.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
  ],
